## ORCHESTRATION PROMPT TEMPLATES

### Spawn a Terminal Subagent
```
Spawn a Terminal Subagent to run the following command and report the output:
[command]
Do not proceed with implementation until you have the output.
```

### Spawn a Docs Subagent
```
Before implementing, spawn a Docs Subagent to:
1. Read @lib/supabase/server.ts and identify the exact createClient pattern used
2. Read @app/api/ and identify the standard route handler structure
3. Report what patterns to follow before any code is written
```

### Spawn a Test Subagent
```
After completing the implementation, spawn a Test Subagent to:
1. Run: npx tsc --noEmit
2. Run: npm test (if tests exist)
3. Report: pass/fail count, any new TypeScript errors
Do not mark this task complete until the Test Subagent reports clean results.
```

### Spawn parallel Refactor Subagents
```
Spawn two Refactor Subagents in parallel:
- Subagent A: Edit ONLY @lib/supabase/server.ts — [specific change]
- Subagent B: Edit ONLY @app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts — [specific change]
These files do not share imports. Safe to parallelize.
Wait for both before continuing.
```

