## GIT WORKTREES — THE PROFESSIONAL APPROACH

For large parallel tasks, use Git worktrees instead of multiple Cursor windows.
Each agent works on its own branch in isolation:

```bash
# Create isolated worktrees for parallel work
git worktree add ../project-auth-fix auth-fix-branch
git worktree add ../project-db-fix db-fix-branch

# Open each in separate Cursor window
# Each agent works completely isolated
# Merge when both are done
```

Benefits over multiple Cursor windows:
- Complete code isolation — no file conflicts possible
- Each worktree has its own `node_modules` state
- Merge via standard git PR process
- Full history preserved per branch

```bash
# Clean up worktrees when done
git worktree remove ../project-auth-fix
git worktree remove ../project-db-fix
```

---

## ⚠️ CRITICAL — REPEATED AT BOTTOM

- **Max 3 subagents** — more causes file conflicts that silently destroy code
- **Parallel only on isolated files** — confirm no shared imports before spawning
- **Always spawn Test Subagent last** — verify the work before declaring done
- **Git commit before any multi-agent task** — rollback point is non-negotiable
- **Sequential by default, parallel only when files are confirmed isolated**

