## AGENT DEFINITION FILES

Pre-built subagent definitions are in `agents/` at the project root.
Reference them by name to delegate specialised tasks:

| Agent | File | When to invoke |
|---|---|---|
| `code-reviewer` | `agents/code-reviewer.md` | After any change — checks all Rocket patterns |
| `planner` | `agents/planner.md` | Before any feature — produces plan.md |
| `database-reviewer` | `agents/database-reviewer.md` | Any data/RLS/schema issue |
| `security-reviewer` | `agents/security-reviewer.md` | Before production or security sweep |
| `build-error-resolver` | `agents/build-error-resolver.md` | Netlify build failures |

**How to invoke**: "Use the code-reviewer agent to review the changes I just made."
